<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
The epithet 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">formicidae</emphasis>
refers to an insect host in family 
<taxonomicName family="Formicidae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="family">Formicidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
Characterized by phialides always being solitary and rather long and narrow, 51-70.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.7-0.9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. Conidia adhering in globose slimy heads, mostly filiform to fusoid, 3.9-7.9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.8-1.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. Octahedral crystals absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
